    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-10-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-10-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="478"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d478">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Dupuy de Lôme</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-10-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 5, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 42.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge your note of the
                    2d instant and to thank you for the contents and especially for the assurance
                    that if the American citizens referred to in my note to you of the 27th ultimo
                    have been annoyed and persecuted by Spanish officials in Cuba, “His Majesty’s
                    Government, which is resolved that the laws shall be respected, both by those
                    who live in Spanish territory and by those who are bound to guard the laws and
                    have them executed, will punish all who have committed any wrong, and will make
                    reparation for it if there has been any.”</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
